sentences: She recorded for Exclusive Records in the 1949.
On March 12, 1940, she married George Thomas in Cleveland, Ohio.
Thomas began performing at Detroit's Four Horsemen Club in 1940.
Thomas was featured with Earl Carroll's Vanities in the spring of 1944 and played eight months at Harry's Show Bar in Detroit.
Through the 1940s, she had appearances at hotels and bars around the country.
In 1949, Thomas recorded four songs for Leon René's Exclusive Records in Los Angeles: "I'm In Town," "Waga-Waga," "I Don't Want Your Money, Honey," and "Lover Man."
Her first single "Waga-Waga" / "I Don't Want Your Money, Honey," was released in June 1949.
Her second single, "I'm In Town" / "Lover Man," was released in September 1949.
That month, Exclusive declared bankruptcy and ceased operations in January 1950.
In the 1950s, Thomas performed gigs around California.
She married Lonnie I. Riggs in 1954.
By the 1960s, Thomas had relocated back to Detroit; she performed around the Midwest.
She died in Detroit on July 5, 1978.
"I'm In Town" was used in the films Men Of Honor (2000), Lonely Hearts (2006), and Trumbo (2015).
